def initSL {a : Type} : (sl : SymList a) → SymList a
| ⟨xs, ys, ok⟩ =>
  if h : ys.isEmpty then
    match xs with
    | [] => nil
    | _  => nil
  else
    if h2 : ys.length = 1 then
     splitInTwoSL xs
    else SymList.mk xs ys.tail (by
      simp [← not_congr List.length_eq_zero_iff] at h
      apply And.intro
      all_goals
       intro h3
       simp [h3] at ok
       cases ys with
       | nil => contradiction
       | cons b bs => simp_all)
```

This defines `initSL` to compute the initial part of a `SymList`. The definition is complex, handling cases where the second list is empty, the second list has length 1, or the second list has length greater than 1.

